{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"24baa6b4-9362-4f7e-bf0c-5cdb6b58b51a","content":"Yes! Modern MSTest (v3.3+) supports **tuple-based `DynamicData`**, eliminating the `object[]` boxing:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]\npublic void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)\n{\n    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);\n    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);\n}\n\npublic static IEnumerable<(string Input, bool Expected)> TestData =>\n[\n    (\"valid@email.com\", true),\n    (\"invalid\", false),\n    (\"\", false),\n];\n```\n\n**What changed:**\n- `IEnumerable<object[]>` → `IEnumerable<(string, bool)>` — compile-time type safety, no casts\n- Array literals `[\"x\", true]` → tuple literals `(\"x\", true)` — typed elements\n\nThe tuple fields are automatically destructured into the test method parameters by position. You get compiler errors if types don't match, rather than runtime `InvalidCastException`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"11d96040-2d31-410e-9136-c6c3fbf0954b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a more type-safe way to write data-driven tests in modern MSTest, replacing the `DynamicData` attribute with `object[]` arrays. Modern MSTest (v3.3+) introduced typed test data sources using tuples and the `[DataSource]` attribute, but more relevantly, MSTest v3.4+ introduced `[DynamicData]` with strongly-typed delegates, and MSTest v3.6+ introduced `[TestDataSource]` with generic type support.\n\nActually, let me think more carefully. The key modern MSTest feature for type-safe data-driven tests is:\n\n\nThe most practical approach in modern MSTest is using `IEnumerable<ValueTuple>` or `IEnumerable<Tuple>` with the `DynamicData` attribute, which lets you return strongly-typed tuples instead of `object[]` arrays, providing compile-time type safety while keeping the syntax clean. Writing test method example... The tuple approach provides compile-time type safety that `object[]` lacks, and this feature has been supported in MSTest 3.6+, making it the cleanest modern solution for parameterized tests.","outputTokens":1282,"requestId":"BD26:2EAB99:1D4A442:2138095:6A07CBBA"},"id":"e634aa57-b50b-4514-8ab0-da60e8afb0f7","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:43:43.766Z","parentId":"f6363edf-a683-4cea-81e9-489194be63af"}
